Package model

Interface Summary
Strategy A Strategy object should have a name, which can identify it to a user, and a takeTurn method.
 

Class Summary
Dice A Dice object consists of a rack of five dice for use in a Yahtzee game.
FourAndUpStrategy The FourAndUpStrategy implements the Strategy interface.
Game A Game object represents an instance of a Yahtzee game.
HumanStrategy The HumanStrategy implements the Strategy interface, and allows human play for a Yahtzee game implementing the Strategy design pattern for computer strategies.
OfAKinderStrategy The OfAKinderStrategy implements the Strategy interface.
Player A Player object represents a player in a Yahtzee game.
PlayerIdentity Represent the immutable player identity for a Player object in a Yahtzee game.
RandomStrategy The RandomStrategy implements the Strategy interface.
Score A Score object represents a single score in a Yahtzee game, including a hand and a numeric score.
ScoreCard A Score Card keeps score for a certain player.
ScoreValidator The ScoreValidator class validates and scores hands for a Yahtzee dice game.
UpperSectionerStrategy The UpperSectionerStrategy implements the Strategy interface.
 

Enum Summary
DiceStatus Enumerates the status of the Dice object
Hands Enumerates the possible hands in a Yahtzee game.
Status Enumerates the status of the Game object
